        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="435" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d435">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>No official record of the conversation at this dinner has been found. The list of
                    those present is derived from the Log, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                        target="#pg_655">p. 655</ref>. <persName corresp="#p_LWD1">Leahy</persName>,
                    p. 212, has the following brief summary: “During the dinner <persName
                        corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_CC2"
                        >Churchill</persName> compared their reactions to <persName
                        corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName> and reviewed the military and political
                    discussion with our Russian ally that had just ended. The Prime Minister clearly
                    indicated that he was inclined toward the American point of view on matters that
                    up to then had produced much controversy between the U. S. and British staffs,
                    particularly on the timing of the cross-Channel attack on Germany.” See also
                        <persName corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName>, p. 408.</p>
            </div>
